urlText: T1 North Shore Line: Trackwork between North Sydney and Wynyard
content:
Friday 1 to Sunday 10 January
  • Buses replace all trains between North Sydney and Wynyard. 
  • Extra ferries also run between Milsons Point and Circular Quay wharves. 
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Hornsby and North Sydney only. 
  • T9 Northern Line trains run between Berowra or Hornsby and Central, platforms 1-12, via Strathfield. 
  • Monday 4 to Friday 8 January, trains run to a weekend timetable with extra trains during the morning and afternoon peak periods. 
  • Daily from 6am until 7pm, express buses also run between North Sydney and Circular Quay (Macquarie St) or Town Hall (Bathurst St). 
  • Check service capacity and allow extra travel time. 
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.

85T1: North Sydney to Town Hall (Bathurst St) and return (weekdays 6am – 7pm only)
86T1: North Sydney to Circular Quay (Macquarie St) and return (weekdays 6am – 7pm only)

urlText: T1 Western Line: Trackwork may affect your travel
content:

  • From 6am Friday 1 January trains run to a changed timetable between Emu Plains or Penrith and the City Circle, from Central first stop Museum. If you are travelling to City Circle stations please remain on the train. 
  • Buses replace T1 North Shore Line trains between Wynyard and North Sydney. 
  • If you are travelling to Milsons Point you can also catch a ferry from Circular Quay wharf. 
  • Richmond trains run to a changed timetable between Richmond and Central, platforms 1-12.

    • Daily from 6am until 7pm, express buses also run from Circular Quay (Macquarie St) or Town Hall (Bathurst St) to North Sydney.

urlText: T1 North Shore Line: Trains run between Berowra and Wynyard only
content:
Saturday 23 and Sunday 24 January
  • Trains run between Berowra and Wynyard only.
  • A shuttle train service also runs between Lindfield and North Sydney.
  • City Circle trains run in one direction only, from Wynyard first stop Circular Quay.
  • T1 Western and T9 Northern Line trains start and end at Central, platforms 1-12.
  • If you are travelling to Town Hall you can catch the light rail.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.

urlText: T1 Western Line: Trackwork may affect your travel
content:
Saturday 23 and Sunday 24 January
  • Penrith trains run to a changed timetable between Emu Plains or Penrith and Central, platforms 1 – 12 only.
  • Richmond trains run between Richmond and Olympic Park only. You may need to change at Parramatta to continue your journey.
  • On Sunday from 6.30am until 10.30am, trains run between Richmond and Strathfield only.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.

urlText: Buses replace the all-stations Homebush trains between Strathfield and Central
content:
Monday 18 to Thursday 21 January
  • Nightly from 9.40pm until 1.30am, buses replace the all-stations Homebush trains between Strathfield and Central.
  • Leppington trains run to a changed timetable, making an extra stop at Homebush but will not stop at Ashfield.
  • Some T1 Western Line trains make extra stops at Homebush and Burwood.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
47T2: Central, then all stations to Strathfield and return
50T2: Lewisham, Petersham, Stanmore then Central and return
53T2: Strathfield, then all stations to Summer Hill, Newtown then Central and return
